text: Last Monday we went to have big lunch with my Lot One family after the store was closure. Both are the staff we very friendly.

Have been visiting for 30+ yrs, the quality and quantity has been fairly if not under, priced affordably.
There was barely noticeable change in taste except getting better since my 1st plate of the dishes.
May not suit everyone's taste buds but I know the 30+ years searching for comparable alternatives have been almost, if not, non-existence.

Excellent Muslim food can be found in this unnoticeable place. (Up on a hill) Nasi lemak and Nasi padang is the best. Ayam penyet (Muslim chicken rice) and even Muslim style Zi-char(煮炒)can be found here. However, the coffee and tea served are far from standard. Otherwise I would have given a 5 star for this comment.
It have Halal western,Malay Rojak,Seafood Halal and Chicken Rice stall. While the drink kinda a limited hot choices. Normal hot drinks only.

Only drink stall dont accept paynow, every other shop accepts it. When recommending to accept paynow, claims boss is not around, payment will hold up the queue (most of the time no queue) and manager just sits around looking at people. Very backwards mentality to change when e-payment can help with accounting and admin.
